# Loyalty Rewards App

A simple, cloud-based loyalty rewards system for small businesses. Customers check in with their phone number, and businesses can easily track visits and reward loyalty.

## Live Demo

[View the Live Demo](https://loyalty-rewards-app-beige.vercel.app/)  


---

## Features

- Fast, contactless customer check-in
- Real-time rewards tracking
- Easy-to-use interface for staff and customers
- Works on any device
- Secure and scalable (React frontend, Node.js/MongoDB backend)

---

## How It Works

1. Customer enters their phone number at checkout.
2. The system logs the visit and tracks rewards.
3. Customers receive rewards after a set number of visits.

---

## Technology Stack

- **Frontend:** React (deployed on Vercel)
- **Backend:** Node.js, Express, MongoDB (deployed on Render)
- **Database:** MongoDB Atlas

---

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Node.js & npm
- MongoDB Atlas account (for database)

### Installation

1. **Clone the repository:**
   ```sh
   git clone https://github.com/x88-code/loyalty-rewards-app.git
   cd loyalty-rewards-app
   ```

2. **Backend Setup:**
   ```sh
   cd server
   npm install
   # Create a .env file with your MongoDB URI
   echo "MONGODB_URI=your-mongodb-uri" > .env
   npm start
   ```

3. **Frontend Setup:**
   ```sh
   cd ../client
   npm install
   npm start
   ```

---

## Environment Variables

- **Backend:**  
  - `MONGODB_URI` — Your MongoDB Atlas connection string

- **Frontend:**  
  - `REACT_APP_API_URL` — URL of your deployed backend (e.g., `https://loyalty-rewards-app.onrender.com`)

---

## Deployment

- **Frontend:** Deploy to [Vercel](https://vercel.com)
- **Backend:** Deploy to [Render](https://render.com) or similar

